But why need 1 weary you with lengthy details of the feast, the dances of maidens, the music, the Pyrrhic dance of the youths in armour, and other entertainments with which Theagenes graced his magnificent banquet, and the exquisite dishes which rendered the repast more agreeable and conduced to conviviality? 1 will, however, tell you things which it is necessary you should know, and which it will give me pleasure to relate. Theagenes assumed a look of cheerfulness, and forced himself to enter· tain the company, but 1 saw in what direction his thoughts were tending. He kept rolling his eyes; from time to time he heaveda deep sigh without any apparent reason3 at one time dejected and deep in thought, he suddenly became more cheer· ful, as if he were conscious of his manner and wished to recover himself ; in short, he passed rapidly from one extreme to the other.
